OL,3,CHow Rachel Reeves may have found #25bn
OL,4,Cbehind the back of the sofa
OL,6,FI've had a chance to examine the
OL,7,Fimplications for her fiscal rules of
OL,8,Fthe chancellor's statements in her
OL,9,Fconference speech, that she would
OL,10,Fsecure growth through increased
OL,11,Finvestment and compel the Treasury to
OL,12,Fgive more weight to the benefits of
OL,13,Fgrowth, rather than focusing
OL,14,Fexcessively on the short-term
OL,15,Fimplications for public sector debt.
OL,17,FIn simple terms, it suggests she will
OL,18,Fannounce a plan in the October 30
OL,19,Fbudget to take investment vehicles
OL,20,Flike the new National Wealth Fund off
OL,21,Fthe public sector balance sheet.
