OL,3,CHow Rachel Reeves may have found #25bn
OL,4,Cbehind the back of the sofa
OL,6,FBut, the fiscal-rules reform won't and
OL,7,Fcan't end the significant pressure on
OL,8,Fday-to-day spending on public-sector
OL,9,Fwages, welfare and the like, because
OL,10,Fone of Reeves's fiscal rules is more
OL,11,Fconstraining than the Tories' version:
OL,12,Fshe is committed over five years
OL,13,F(again) to cover all day-today
OL,14,Fspending with tax revenues.
OL,16,FBottom line?
